When this rule is mentioned use this documentation:

# Value Providers

By attaching "value providers" to types, you can enable the platform to retrieve possible values for the fields in which those types are used.

As an example:

We have a connector with this function which retrieves the population for a given country:

```dataweave
var getPopulation : Operation<{country: CountryIsoCode}> = {
    // ...
}
```
Suppose the "country" parameter expects to receive an _ISO code_ (e.g., AR, US, BR).
It wouldn't be nice to ask the user to remember which ISO code belongs to each country.
We can define a value provider to do that.

We need to create a value provider:
```dataweave
var getCountries = // ...

var countriesValueProvider = defineValueProvider(
    getCountries.executor,
    (response: HttpResponse<{items: Array<Country>}>) ->
        response.body.items map ((item, index) -> {value: item.isoCode, displayValue: { label: item.name}})
)
```
This value provider will call `getCountries` operation (through its executor) to retrieve a list of countries.
This list cannot be used as is, we need to extract the data we need for the value provider.
That what's the second parameter to defineValueProvider does, it provides a
transformation function that goes from the executor output to a list of objects.
Each of these objects must have the following structure:

```dataweave
{
    value: VALUE // the actual value that will be sent as input
    displayValue: {
        value: LABEL // a label to show to the user, corresponding to the value above
    }
}
```

We now need to include the newly created value provider in the connector declaration, like this:
```dataweave
@FlowConnectorElement()
var connector = {
    name: "WorldInfo",
    // ...
    operations: {
       getPopulation: getPopulation,
       getCountries: getCountries
    },
    valueProviders: {
        countriesValueProvider: countriesValueProvider,
    }
}
```

Now, we have a value provider which can be referenced from different operations that receive a country as input.

This operation for getting the population for a country defines a value provider for its parameter:
```dataweave
var getPopulation : Operation<{country: @ValuesFrom(value = { name: countriesValueProvider }) CountryIsoCode}> = {
    // ...
}
```

More details about referencing a value provider can be found in the [providers documentation](./uc-providers.mdc).
